article.headline: Penn State 69, Sacred Heart 61
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Aaron Johnson scored 18 points and grabbed 20 rebounds to lead Penn State to a 69-61 victory over Sacred Heart on Saturday. The Nittany Lions (3-2) used a 14-3 run and held Sacred Heart without a field goal for nearly 8½ minutes in the second half before sealing the win in the final minutes from the free-throw line. Joey Henley led Sacred Heart (1-3) with 14 points and nine rebounds. Sacred Heart slowly chipped away in the final minutes, holding the Lions scoreless from the floor in the final 6:52, but Penn State went 10-for-16 from the line in the final 3½ minutes. Though the Nittany Lions shot just 31.3 percent from the field, they had 20 offensive rebounds. Mike Walker went 4-for-7 from 3-point range for 15 points for Penn State, and Marlon Smith and Danny Morrissey each finished with 11 points. Ryon Howard and Luke Granato both scored 11 points for Sacred Heart. Granato hit a 3, pulling Sacred Heart within one midway through the second half, but Johnson started Penn State's run with a layup and Morrissey added a 3-pointer. Another breakaway layup by Smith gave Penn State a 53-43 lead with 8:36 left. Penn State held a 53-44 rebounding edge.
